      <title>Modeline in vim</title>
      <link>https://aheimsbakk.github.io/post/20140413-modeline/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 13 Apr 2014 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>arnulf.heimsbakk@gmail.com (Arnulf Heimsbakk)</author>
      <guid>https://aheimsbakk.github.io/post/20140413-modeline/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Options set in &lt;code&gt;.vimrc&lt;/code&gt; applies to all vim files. You can use modelines to set specific vim options for one file. Modeline option must be set in &lt;code&gt;.vimrc&lt;/code&gt; to take advantage of this option.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
